<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="754" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d754">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/23427.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Mediators</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-08">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 8, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge
                            receipt of the note of your excellencies communicating a cablegram which
                            you have received from General Huerta. In reply I beg to say that the
                            troops and munitions mentioned were sent only to Vera Cruz, a place
                            occupied by the United States when your offer of mediation was accepted.
                            I am pleased to inform your excellencies that no aggressive measures of
                            any kind have been taken by this Government since the acceptance of your
                            generous good offices and that nothing has been done in conflict with
                            the understanding with your excellencies as to suspension of
                            hostilities.</p>
                        <p>I avail [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>